  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 16-19.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - These verses have a re-enumeration of the three sons of Levi, and differ from the enumeration of ver. 1, in being followed by the sons of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "each",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of these three, and afterwards by the line of descendants from each, instead of by the sons of only one, Kohath, and his descendant in only one stem, the high priest stem, and with only one object. All these names agree with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 6:17-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 3:17-20",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (comp. also ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 3:21-36",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " with Numbers 26:57-60), with the trifling exceptions already alluded to, in the Hebrew spelling of Gershom and the Authorized Version spelling of Shimei and the Authorized Version Mahali of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Exodus 6:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". The latter half of ver. 19, according to the Hebrew, should rather refer to what has preceded, and be a \"subscription,\" though it might best suit the connection to regard it as introducing what was to follow, and as being a \"superscription.\" Bertheau holds with the former of these views, Keil with the latter. 1 Chronicles 6:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Keil and Delitzsch Biblical Commentary on the Old Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "(Ch. 6). The families and cities of the Levites. - Vv. 1-34. Register of the families of the Levites. - This is introduced by an enumeration of the sons and grandsons of Levi (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 6:16-19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), which is followed by lists of families in six lines of descent: (a) the descendants of Gershon (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 6:20-21",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), of Kohath (",
        "children": []
      },
